Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

== Couscous ==

Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour the @water for the couscous{240%ml} from your kettle into the bowl and stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}.

Cover tightly with #cling film{} and leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Honey Chermoula Beef ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and fry until starting to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @chermoula spice mix{1} and @lemon & herb seasoning{1} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%jar} and remaining chicken stock paste. Bring to a boil, then lower to a simmer.

Cook until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Meanwhile, once the couscous is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{}.

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, the lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Stir to combine.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @honey{15%g} and a squeeze of lemon juice to the beef mixture.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Cook until glossy, ~{1%minute}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share your lemon couscous between your plates and top with the honey chermoula beef.

Finish with a scattering of the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g}.

Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!